                ],
                "institute": "2JPNKTO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THE 46 MEV ELECTRON LINAC AT THE",
                " RESEARCH REACTOR INSTITUTE OF KYOTO UNIVERSITY, OPER-",
                " ATED AT A FREQUENCY OF 240 - 250 PULSES/SEC."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "PHOTO"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " BURSTS OF NEUTRONS WERE PRODUCED FROM THE",
                " WATER-COOLED PHOTONEUTRON TARGET, WHICH WERE MADE OF",
                " SEVERAL SHEETS OF TA PLATES, 5 CM BY 5 CM SQUARE WITH",
                " AN EFFECTIVE TOTAL THICKNESS OF ABOUT 3.5 CM. THE TAR-",
                " GET WAS PLACED IN THE CENTER OF AN OCTAGONAL WATER",
                " TANK, 30 CM IN DIAMETER AND 8 CM THICK, TO MODERATE",
                " THE NEUTRON ENERGIES. A 7 CM DIAMETER BY 20 CM THICK",
                " PB BLOCK WAS PLACED IN THE FLIGHT PATH TO SUPPRESS THE",
                " PROMPT GAMMA-FLASH. THE NEUTRONS WERE COLLIMATED TO A",
                " 4 CM DIAMETER AT THE SAMPLE POSITION BY B4C AND PB",
                " COLLIMATORS. OVERLAP OF THERMAL NEUTRONS FROM THE",
                " PREVIOUS PULSES WAS SUPPRESSED USING A 0.5 MM CD",
                " FILTER IN THE NEUTRON BEAM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".SIX SAMPLE THICKNESSES OF POWDERED NATURAL SB WITH A",
                " PURITY OF 99.9%, PACKED IN A CYLINDRICAL ACRYL CASE",
                " WITH AL WINDOWS."
              ]
            }
          ],
